### HYMN CXIII

#### A woman's incantation against a rival

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_0711301">1</span></span>Rough Plant,
thou rough rude parasite, cut thou that man, O  
  Rough and Rude,  
  That thou mayst hinder from his act that man in all his manly  
   strength.  
<span class="margnote"><span id="an_0711302">2</span></span>Thou, rugged
Plant, art rude and rough, Vishā, Vishātaki art  
   thou.  
  That thou mayest be cast off by him, as by a bull a barren cow.

